ZH: 我今天看了一百页的书。
EN: I read one hundred pages of a book today.

ZH: 他已经学会了百家姓。
EN: He has already learned the hundred family names.

ZH: 我已经听了百遍这首歌。
EN: I have listened to this song a hundred times.

ZH: 这个村庄有百家民宿。
EN: This village has a hundred homestays.

ZH: 你能数到一百吗？
EN: Can you count up to one hundred?

ZH: 我买了一百克的咖啡豆。
EN: I bought one hundred grams of coffee beans.

ZH: 他的成绩在班里排前百分之十。
EN: His grades are in the top ten percent of the class.

ZH: 这个宾馆有百余间客房。
EN: This hotel has over a hundred rooms.

ZH: 在中国，百合被视为吉祥之花。
EN: In China, the lily is regarded as a flower of good fortune.

ZH: 他将百分之九十的时间用于学习。
EN: He spends ninety percent of his time studying.

ZH: 这个地方的风景美不胜收，每景每色。
EN: The scenery of this place is incredibly beautiful, with every scene and every color.

ZH: 他百思不得其解，不知道为什么突然得到这个机会。
EN: He was puzzled and couldn't figure out why he suddenly got this opportunity.

ZH: 出师宴上，百舌鸟唱出了美好的祝福。
EN: During the graduation banquet, the nightingale sang beautiful blessings.

ZH: 我们只差百里就能到达目的地了。
EN: We are only a hundred miles away from the destination.

ZH: 他百无聊赖地坐在那儿，无所事事。
EN: He sat there bored, with nothing to do.

ZH: 在这场比赛中，百发百中是我的目标。
EN: In this competition, my goal is to hit the target every single time.

ZH: 他是一个百无聊赖的人，从不对任何事情感兴趣。
EN: He is a person who is bored with everything and never shows interest in anything.

ZH: 他们商量了好几百遍，还是没有达成一致。
EN: They discussed it hundreds of times but still did not come to an agreement.

ZH: 这颗星星闪烁着百种颜色。
EN: This star twinkles with a hundred different colors.

ZH: 这本书有百万字。
EN: This book contains a million words.
